In [73]:
# import the v1 library
mylib1 = setup.Setup(x,y)

# choose features
mylib1.choose_features(name = 'multilayer_perceptron',layer_sizes = [1,10,10,10,10,1],activation = 'tanh')

# choose normalizer
mylib1.choose_normalizer(name = 'standard')

# choose cost
mylib1.choose_cost(name = 'least_squares')

# fit an optimization
mylib1.fit(max_its = 10000,alpha_choice = 10**(-1),train_portion = 0.5)

# plot cost history
mylib1.show_histories(start = 0)
